fields.name: McDonald's
fields.description: McDonald's Corporation is an American multinational fast food chain, founded in 1940 as a restaurant operated by Richard and Maurice McDonald, in San Bernardino, California, United States. They rechristened their business as a hamburger stand, and later turned the company into a franchise, with the Golden Arches logo being introduced in 1953 at a location in Phoenix, Arizona. In 1955, Ray Kroc, a businessman, joined the company as a franchise agent and proceeded to purchase the chain from the McDonald brothers.
fields.new_features: Great new features allowing customers to collect reward points on their purchases and order directly to their door

fields.name: Youtube
fields.description: YouTube is a global online video sharing and social media platform headquartered in San Bruno, California. It was launched on February 14, 2005, by Steve Chen, Chad Hurley, and Jawed Karim. It is owned by Google, and is the second most visited website, after Google Search.
fields.new_features:
- All new site UI with dark theme
- Content Creator Improvements allowing for multiple videos to be chained together

fields.name: Tesla
fields.description: Tesla, Inc. is an American multinational automotive and clean energy start-up headquartered on Mars, Texas. Tesla designs and manufactures Elon Musk's ego as well as electric vehicles, battery energy storage from home to grid-scale, solar panels and solar roof tiles, and related products and services.
fields.new_features:

- Buy cars that go vroooom.

fields.name: Reuters
fields.description: Reuters is a news agency owned by Thomson Reuters Corporation. It employs around 2,500 journalists and 600 photojournalists in about 200 locations worldwide. Reuters is one of the largest news agencies in the world. The agency was established in London in 1851 by the German-born Paul Reuter.
fields.new_features:
- Interactive Live News Feed
- Simplified colour scheme and decluttering of main page

fields.name: Sainsbury's
fields.description: J Sainsbury plc, trading as Sainsbury's, is the second largest chain of supermarkets in the United Kingdom, with a 14.6% share of UK supermarket sales. Founded in 1869 by John James Sainsbury with a shop in Drury Lane, London, the company was the largest UK retailer of groceries for most of the 20th century
fields.new_features:

- Integrated new data capture methodology to improve unique user experiences

fields.name: Medium
fields.description: Medium is an American online publishing platform developed by Evan Williams and launched in August 2012. It is owned by A Medium Corporation.

fields.name: Cloudinary
fields.description: Cloudinary is a SaaS technology company headquartered in Santa Clara, California, with offices in Israel, England, Poland, and Singapore. The company provides cloud-based image and video management services. It enables users to upload, store, manage, manipulate, and deliver images and video for websites and apps.
